snippet.textDisplay: Hands Down, the Coke Studio seasons from across the border have time and again demonstrated the depth, diversity and talent of the Pakistani singers. I hope the rest of the world (including us on this side of the border) realize, appreciate and acknowledge the immense artistic talent that Pakistan has produced over the years. There is so much that this country can offer the world and yet the world seems hell bent on branding the rather culturally rich country for all reasons wrong. We (on both sides of the border) need to shed the idea of letting thy neighbour rot, since we would then only be ensuring that we would have to live in a rotting neighbourhood. Open the borders, let the common man and woman meet, build bonds and quash prejudices - this is when we will realize we have too much in common and too little by way of differences. Lastly but most importantly, this song by Meesha and Naeem is just amazing!
